txt.en:
'We cannot allow Shelob's children to gain a greater foothold in Cirith Ungol, [placeholder]. It seems that Shelob seeks to expand her lair into the depths of the Tower, and that spells doom for the hope of keeping her children from flooding into the other lands of Mordor and beyond.

'As with the webs of Shelob herself at Torech Ungol, the webs of her children are thick, but vulnerable to flame.

'Burn any webs you find, and push Shelob's children back into the Ephel DÃºath!'
As webs begin to fill the Tower of Cirith Ungol, it has become clear that Shelob now desires to expand her lair into the Tower.
Although spiders still flood into Cirith Ungol, you have burned many of their webs and prevented them from gaining a greater foothold in the Tower of Cirith Ungol.
Webs can be found throughout Cirith Ungol.\n\nLegolas has asked you to burn webs to prevent the spiders from gaining a foothold in Cirith Ungol.
You have burned many webs in Cirith Ungol.
